alley
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a marble
Origin:
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: 1881 but prob. since 1940s obs: (but cf American alley), OED 1720; DARE US 1848, now confined chiefly to the NE states; EDD the ring in  which some marble games are played.] [AND alley 2. phrs. 1924.]  make one's alley good (with) var. of to make one's marble good, to ingratiate onself (with); to improve one's prospects.
